Website Structure
The website consists of several sections:
Home Page
Navigation Bar
Product Categories
Product Listings
Product Detail Pages
Footer
Each section is connected through navigation links, allowing users to move easily between different pages.
How It Works
Step 1 – Homepage
When the website opens, users are welcomed by the homepage, which displays the store name, navigation menu, and featured electronic products.
Step 2 – Navigation
The navigation bar allows users to move between different pages such as:
Home
Products
Categories
About
Contact
Clicking a menu option loads the corresponding webpage.
Step 3 – Product Categories
Products are organized into categories such as:
Laptops
Smartphones
Accessories
Headphones
Smart Devices
Users can browse products by selecting a category.
Step 4 – Product Listing
Each product displays:
Product Image
Product Name
Price
Short Description
This layout makes it easier for users to compare products.
Step 5 – Product Details
When a user selects a product, detailed information is displayed, including:
Product Name
Description
Price
Features
Product Image
This simulates a real e-commerce website.
Step 6 – User Experience
The website is designed with a simple and organized layout, making navigation easy. The clean interface improves readability and provides a smooth browsing experience.
